hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I've lost my bank card arize pills Criado-Perez led the charge for women on the reverse of Bank of England notes after the decision to replace Elizabeth Fry with Winston Churchill on the £5 note. She gained the support of more than 35,000 petitioners and raised money for a legal challenge citing the Equality Act 2010. In the end Bank of England Governor Mark Carney caved in and announced that Jane Austen will appear on new £10 notes from 2017. During the campaign she received a lot of online abuse, particularly on Twitter, which led to death threats and subsequent arrests.
